12.20	Ebenezer_Butterick	Ebenezer Butterick	In 1867 Butterick began publishing a magazine to promote their patterns, the Ladies Quarterly of Broadway Fashions, which was followed, in 1868, with the monthly Metropolitan. Both magazines offered fashion news and advice, as well as mail order services for Butterick's designs. In 1873, E. Butterick &amp; Co. began publishing The Delineator, which, by the turn of the century, became the premiere women's fashion magazine in the US.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/TheDelineatorAugust1894.JPG/220px-TheDelineatorAugust1894.JPG
